Bye, sweetie.

01:38.719 --> 01:41.015
♪ the hollow sound is ringing
where your heart used to be ♪

01:41.015 --> 01:45.015
♪ have you found that your
admiration will never set you free ♪

01:45.807 --> 01:49.278
(sighs)

01:55.807 --> 01:59.807
(Sighs)

02:01.446 --> 02:04.349
I had that horrible dream again.

02:04.349 --> 02:07.932
I was trapped inside a giant
mummy's foot with Madonna,

02:07.932 --> 02:09.934
and she wouldn't stop singing.

02:09.934 --> 02:12.837
I hate that dream, on many levels.

02:12.837 --> 02:14.806
Well, I reached over to find
you, but you weren't there.

02:14.806 --> 02:16.941
Oh. I'm sorry, babe.

02:16.941 --> 02:20.511
Just been up since 5:00 trying
to get through this work.

02:20.511 --> 02:21.546
Mm.

02:21.546 --> 02:23.481
And now I'm running late, so...

02:23.481 --> 02:24.782
- Uh-huh.
- Mmm.

02:24.782 --> 02:26.017
- Mmm.
- Mmm.

02:26.017 --> 02:28.186
Whoa. Whoa. Come here.

02:28.186 --> 02:29.787
Hmm?

02:29.787 --> 02:30.822
Your breath.

02:30.822 --> 02:32.523
Oh, no. Is it bad?

02:32.523 --> 02:33.858
No. No. No. It's just...
it's... it's different.

02:33.858 --> 02:35.681
My breath is different?

02:35.681 --> 02:36.983
Yeah. It's weird.

02:36.983 --> 02:38.651
You been chewing on pennies or something?

02:38.651 --> 02:40.353
- What?
- Yeah.

02:40.353 --> 02:42.088
- Okay, now you are freaking me out.
- No. Come on. Kiss me again.

02:42.088 --> 02:43.589
- Oh.
- Just once.

02:45.658 --> 02:46.659
Uh-huh.

02:46.659 --> 02:48.527
Uh-huh. Okay.

02:48.527 --> 02:49.562
Bye.

02:49.562 --> 02:50.763
Bye.

02:50.763 --> 02:51.764
Love you.

02:51.764 --> 02:54.467
(Chuckles)

02:54.467 --> 02:56.402
(Knock on door)

02:56.402 --> 02:57.803
Hello!

02:57.803 --> 02:59.305
I know I'm late but...

02:59.305 --> 03:01.340
Oh! Ooh! I'm sorry. I'll wait outside.

03:01.340 --> 03:03.342
Oh, Alex, don't be silly.

03:03.342 --> 03:04.777
He's out cold. See?

03:07.079 --> 03:08.447
That's impressive.

03:08.447 --> 03:09.982
Mm-hmm.

03:09.982 --> 03:12.551
Well, it looks like you guys
had a lot of fun last night.

03:12.551 --> 03:13.786
Yeah, as much fun as you can have

03:13.786 --> 03:15.688
with someone that only watches cartoons.

03:15.688 --> 03:16.956
When they're that pretty,

03:16.956 --> 03:18.391
generally, they're not that interesting.

03:18.391 --> 03:19.725
Doesn't bother you?

03:19.725 --> 03:22.328
Mm. It's a trade-off. So how are you?

03:22.328 --> 03:23.396
You know, I'm okay.

03:23.396 --> 03:25.398
Are you still breaking up with Sally?

03:25.398 --> 03:27.033
Because it's been, like, a week.

03:27.033 --> 03:29.301
Well, we were together for five years.

03:29.301 --> 03:31.037
I mean, you know, there's a lot of history.

03:31.037 --> 03:33.906
Yeah, but how many times can
you have the same conversation

03:33.906 --> 03:35.341
over and over and over again?

03:35.341 --> 03:37.443
It's never exactly the same.

03:37.443 --> 03:39.378
Oh, but it doesn't matter anyways.

03:39.378 --> 03:40.646
Sally and I are

03:40.646 --> 03:44.784
officially, officially
over as of last night.

03:44.784 --> 03:47.019
Oh, sweetheart.

03:47.019 --> 03:49.855
I'm sorry. Now I feel
like a jerk. Are you okay?

03:49.855 --> 03:51.524
Yeah. No, I'm fine.

03:51.524 --> 03:54.060
It's hard, you know, but I know
it was the right thing to do.

03:55.394 --> 03:56.862
I'm moving out tomorrow.

03:56.862 --> 03:58.564
(Gasps) You found a place already?

03:58.564 --> 04:02.001
Mm-hmm. It's not great. I
really can't afford much,

04:02.001 --> 04:03.335
but it's close to the yoga studio,

04:03.335 --> 04:06.405
and I was wondering if you wouldn't mind

04:06.405 --> 04:08.507
helping me move my stuff.

04:08.507 --> 04:09.542
Of course.

04:09.542 --> 04:11.077
(Chuckles)

04:11.077 --> 04:12.845
And, you know, if you're too sad to hike,

04:12.845 --> 04:14.547
I totally understand.

04:14.547 --> 04:16.982
Not so fast, lazybones.

04:16.982 --> 04:19.385
(Flaps lips) Mm.

04:21.320 --> 04:24.356
Ugh. I hate when you're
silent. Whenever you're silent,

04:24.356 --> 04:26.025
it means I have less money than I thought.

04:28.961 --> 04:30.596
You have less money than you thought.

04:30.596 --> 04:31.997
W... how can that be?

04:31.997 --> 04:34.600
What happened to the $500,000
from Paul's life insurance?

04:34.600 --> 04:36.001
Well, a big chunk went to cover

04:36.001 --> 04:37.970
the debts you accrued
over the last three years.

04:37.970 --> 04:39.805
You sunk a large sum into the shop.

04:39.805 --> 04:41.907
To build a business so that
I could settle those debts.

04:41.907 --> 04:44.043
I mean, not to mention
make a life for myself...

04:44.043 --> 04:45.811
on your advice, I might add.

04:45.811 --> 04:48.013
You're my most responsible client, April.

04:48.013 --> 04:49.682
You've done all the right things,

04:49.682 --> 04:54.053
but we knew it would be tight
until the store really took off.

04:54.053 --> 04:56.088
So why do you need this money anyway?

04:57.188 --> 04:58.624
There's this friend

04:58.624 --> 05:00.392
who's going through some tough times.

05:00.392 --> 05:03.863
She asked for a loan. I want to help.

05:03.863 --> 05:07.399
Well, you could pull money
out of Lucy's college fund,

05:07.399 --> 05:08.767
but there are penalties.

05:08.767 --> 05:10.002
Absolutely not. I'm not
touching Lucy's money.

05:10.002 --> 05:12.571
We'll just have to find it somewhere else.

05:12.571 --> 05:13.973
How good a friend are
we talking about here?

05:16.008 --> 05:17.910
It's not so much for the friend.

05:17.910 --> 05:20.379
I... oh.

05:20.379 --> 05:21.914
She has a kid, okay?

05:21.914 --> 05:23.916
An innocent kid. He's only 3,

05:23.916 --> 05:26.318
and she can't afford
a decent school for him

05:26.318 --> 05:28.921
- or health insurance.
- (Cell phone rings)

05:28.921 --> 05:30.022
Excuse me.

05:31.924 --> 05:33.526
Hello?

05:33.526 --> 05:35.561
Yes, this is Lucy's mom.

05:35.561 --> 05:36.929
Is everything okay?

05:38.804 --> 05:40.205
I'm coming right now.

05:40.205 --> 05:42.074
What is it? What's wrong?

05:42.074 --> 05:45.511
Uh, Lucy didn't show up for school today.

05:45.511 --> 05:49.114
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I have to go.

05:49.114 --> 05:50.716
(Lila) Oh, she's here.

05:50.716 --> 05:54.019
It's about time. I've been
waiting for about eight minutes.

05:54.019 --> 05:55.454
Why? What's been going on?

05:55.454 --> 05:57.523
You've been asked to be the keynote speaker

05:57.523 --> 06:00.225
at the N.A.F.P.A. center
for mental health symposium.

06:00.225 --> 06:02.761
"To honor your work in
extending mental health

06:02.761 --> 06:04.163
and developmental services

06:04.163 --> 06:06.865
to the diverse communities of Los Angeles.

06:06.865 --> 06:10.035
Other participants include
Mayor Antonio Villaraigosa,

06:10.035 --> 06:12.638
Secretary of State Hillary Clinton"...

06:12.638 --> 06:15.574
(Gasps) Oh, my God. Hillary Clinton?

06:15.574 --> 06:16.675
- Mm-hmm.
- I know!

06:16.675 --> 06:17.710
I can't believe...

06:17.710 --> 06:19.745
Are you sure this was meant for me?

06:19.745 --> 06:21.146
As much as I'd love to take credit,

06:21.146 --> 06:23.215
I'm pretty sure I'm not the one

06:23.215 --> 06:25.984
who "launched the first
program for Korean immigrants,

06:25.984 --> 06:27.019
which was used as a"...

06:27.019 --> 06:28.821
"As a model for similar initiatives

06:28.821 --> 06:30.089
in non-English-speaking communities

06:30.089 --> 06:31.757
in Southern California."

06:31.757 --> 06:34.693
Well, when you say it like that,
it does sound pretty impressive.

06:34.693 --> 06:36.662
Congratulations, Dr. Kim.

06:36.662 --> 06:37.930
It is an incredible honor,

06:37.930 --> 06:39.765
and richly deserved, I might add.

06:39.765 --> 06:41.800
Nice try, Lila, but I'm
gonna be her plus-one.

06:41.800 --> 06:43.502
Major crush on Hillary.

06:43.597 --> 06:44.865
Don't ask.

06:44.865 --> 06:46.667
Everyone has their cross to bear.

06:46.667 --> 06:48.602
Am I interrupting something?

06:48.602 --> 06:51.205
Mr. Newsome, what are...

06:51.205 --> 06:53.106
I wasn't expecting you.

06:53.106 --> 06:54.641
I know. Do you have a minute?

07:02.783 --> 07:04.117
Is he a patient?

07:04.117 --> 07:05.953
Nope.

07:05.953 --> 07:07.054
(Elevator bell dings)

07:07.054 --> 07:09.623
(Cell phone rings)

07:09.623 --> 07:11.558
- (Dominic) So the guy actually writes this.
- (Woman laughs)

07:11.558 --> 07:13.894
No, he writes this. He puts it in writing.

07:13.894 --> 07:15.329
Who does that?

07:15.329 --> 07:18.131
(Laughs)

07:18.131 --> 07:19.600
(Dominic speaks indistinctly)

07:19.600 --> 07:21.568
(Cell phone rings)

07:21.568 --> 07:22.836
Hello?

07:22.836 --> 07:24.872
I think I figured out your weird breath.

07:24.872 --> 07:26.139
Okay. You need a hobby.

07:26.139 --> 07:27.708
Get your ass to the gym.

07:27.708 --> 07:29.710
I'm on my way, actually.

07:29.710 --> 07:31.211
But listen to this...

07:31.211 --> 07:34.047
according to this web
site, metallic breath is

07:34.047 --> 07:36.283
one of the potential signs of pregnancy,

07:36.283 --> 07:39.753
along with, um, fatigue, headaches,

07:39.753 --> 07:41.088
and waking up your husband

07:41.088 --> 07:44.992
four times a night to pee.

07:44.992 --> 07:46.860
Oy. You still there?

07:46.860 --> 07:49.062
Yeah. Yeah. Yeah.

07:49.062 --> 07:50.564
I'm... I'm here.

07:50.564 --> 07:51.665
What do you think?

07:51.665 --> 07:54.134
Well...

07:54.134 --> 07:57.037
I mean, I... I guess it's
definitely a possibility.

07:57.037 --> 07:58.672
Well, given our recent conversations,

07:58.672 --> 08:01.008
I know it might not be exactly
what you want to hear, but...

08:01.008 --> 08:02.676
It's not that, sweetie.

08:02.676 --> 08:05.045
I... I just didn't want you to
get your hopes up all over again.

08:05.045 --> 08:06.713
Babe, my only hope is for us

08:06.713 --> 08:08.882
to be happy, healthy, and in love forever.

08:08.882 --> 08:10.817
Me, too.

08:10.817 --> 08:12.119
I just... I had to tell you.

08:12.119 --> 08:14.555
I mean, what if, right?

08:14.555 --> 08:16.623
(Inhales deeply) Wild.

08:16.623 --> 08:18.759
Anyway, we'll talk more later.

08:18.759 --> 08:19.960
Okay?

08:23.731 --> 08:26.233
You ever considered putting any
chairs in front of your desk?

08:26.233 --> 08:28.268
It might help these conversations.

08:28.268 --> 08:32.339
I'm expecting a patient
any minute, Mr. Newsome.

08:32.339 --> 08:33.941
Why are you here?

08:33.941 --> 08:35.208
There's been a new development

08:35.208 --> 08:36.943
in the Thomas Grey investigation.

08:38.212 --> 08:39.980
What kind of development?

08:39.980 --> 08:42.082
Well, I can't share specifics,
but I'm gonna need your notes

08:42.082 --> 08:44.318
in the months leading
up to Thomas Grey's death

08:44.318 --> 08:46.954
to help clarify his state
of mind before he died.

08:46.954 --> 08:48.288
I already told you his state of mind

08:48.288 --> 08:49.990
the last time you were here.

08:49.990 --> 08:52.059
What can I say? They'd
prefer it in writing.

08:52.059 --> 08:54.261
Well, I'm not comfortable with that.

08:54.261 --> 08:55.763
Why not?

08:55.763 --> 08:58.265
Doctor/patient
confidentiality, for one thing.

08:58.265 --> 08:59.266
I don't want to sound disrespectful,

08:59.266 --> 09:00.834
but the man's dead.

09:00.834 --> 09:03.237
I really don't see him having a problem.

09:03.237 --> 09:07.041
It's a problem because I respect
the privacy of my patients

09:07.041 --> 09:09.009
and the sanctity of
the work I do with them.

09:09.009 --> 09:10.210
Listen, I'm not interested

09:10.210 --> 09:12.012
in anything that doesn't
pertain to this case.

09:12.012 --> 09:14.114
I don't care about the
man's dirty little secrets.

09:15.983 --> 09:18.085
We're done here.

09:21.055 --> 09:23.257
Look, you want me to respect your job.

09:23.257 --> 09:25.626
This is my job. If you
don't want to cooperate,

09:25.626 --> 09:27.261
I have to come back with a subpoena.

09:27.261 --> 09:28.929
I doubt the police would get involved

09:28.929 --> 09:30.631
with a life insurance claim.

09:30.631 --> 09:32.833
That's true, but the new
evidence that we've discovered

09:32.833 --> 09:35.302
may turn this into a
criminal investigation.

09:38.038 --> 09:40.941
Do you still want to
hold on to those notes?

09:40.941 --> 09:43.277
I think I'm gonna have to.

09:52.935 --> 09:57.306
(Sighs)

09:57.306 --> 09:59.007
Naked guy is gone.

09:59.007 --> 10:00.876
And he made the bed. How sweet.

10:00.876 --> 10:04.780
No note. Thank God.

10:04.780 --> 10:06.014
Okay. Mm.

10:06.014 --> 10:08.884
I am gonna hop in the shower.

10:08.884 --> 10:10.719
You pick a place for brunch.

10:10.719 --> 10:12.488
Okay.

